\par \plain\f2\fs24\b 8.0\tab NETWORK TROUBLESHOOTING
\par \plain\f2\fs20 
\par Should you have any difficulties running Worms Armageddon over network, please check below for common problems and solutions. If you continue to experience difficulties, contact the Team17 support department.
\par 
\par \pard\li720\ri-37\fi-720\plain\lang1033\f2\fs20\cf1\b\i 8.1\tab \plain\f2\fs20\cf1\b\i General Network Information
\par \pard\ri-37\plain\f2\fs20\cf1\b\i 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf1\i Recommendations
\par \pard\li360\ri-37\fi-360\tx360{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\plain\f2\fs20 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Worms Armageddon supports connection methods under both the IPX and TCP/IP protocols. These are accessible from the network connection screen. We do however recommend that if you have an IP address available that you choose TCP/IP protocol over IPX as your particular method of connection especially over LAN. This will enable you to ensure that you receive the maximum performance possible from your network games.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}If you encounter any network problems whatsoever please establish that you actually have a viable connection under your chosen protocol. We have listed basic details on possible causes and solutions under each protocol later in this section. However, if you are in any doubt at all on the reliability of your connection please contact your network administrator or ISP for assistance.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}If you are experiencing problems with connection it is possible that your network could include devices such as switches, routers, bridges or firewalls within its structure. In this instance contact your network administrator for a viable solution or consult the firewall support section later in this section.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}Ensure that the Host machine for network play has the highest specification and the fastest available network connection. As this machine manages information for the Client players you may experience possible slowdown or unacceptable game framerate if this is not followed.
\par {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}If you are experiencing slowdown with a large amount of players or spectators please reduce the level of entrants to the game accordingly. 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf2 {\pntext\f1\'b7\tab}ALWAYS\plain\f2\fs20  connect to the closest possible server available within your locale. 
\par \pard\ri-37\plain\f2\fs20\cf0 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs20\cf2\b Note:\plain\f2\fs20\cf2  Team17 Software Ltd is unable to guarantee that all game servers will be available 100% of the time. Should a server fail, then it will restart as soon as possible. We have attempted to make the server connections as reliable as possible.\plain\f2\fs20\cf2\b 
\par \pard\ri-37\plain\f2\fs20\cf0 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs20\cf1\i Ingame Chat Menu 
\par \plain\f2\fs20 Using the PgDn key will open the in-game chat menu box. Similarly the PgUp key will remove it from view. It is also possible to chat directly to other players and spectators via the 'F' keys while the chat box is in use. 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\b 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf1\i Local Area Network problems
\par \plain\f2\fs20 Ensure that you have the correct protocols and network libraries installed and working prior to play. If your machine is on a local area network, please check with your network administrator to rule out any problems.
\par 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf1\i Firewall support
\par \plain\f2\fs20 In addition to the firewall settings being set in the server configuration, the firewall administrator must make available port 6667 (outgoing) and the high ports (client side).
\par 
\par WORMNET uses both Http (World Wide Web) and IRC (Internet Relay Chat) protocols, the IRC protocol uses a single TCP socket connecting to port 6667 on the server (client port is normally a random high port).
\par \pard\ri-37\plain\f2\fs20\cf0 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf1\b\i 8.2\tab IPX / SPX Protocol\plain\f2\fs20\cf1\i 
\par 
\par IPX / SPX Protocol LAN Connection\plain\f2\fs20\cf4 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf2 Please note that it is not possible to play a game of Worms Armageddon under IPX protocol via the Internet. Although IPX can exist in some form on the Internet with the help of programs such as Kali, Worms Armageddon will only work on true IPX networks. If you wish to play via the Internet please refer to the TCP/IP Protocol Connection later in this section.
\par \plain\f2\fs20\b 
\par \plain\f2\fs20 It is strongly advisable that games are played under an identical IPX / SPX connection environment. Machines must have the same frame type and if possible the same network drivers also. Worms Armageddon has been tested extensively under drivers such as the Microsoft\plain\f4\fs20 \'e2\plain\f2\fs20  IPX / SPX compatible protocol for Windows 95 / 98 and Novell\plain\f4\fs20 \'e2\plain\f2\fs20  IPX ODI protocol and these are highly recommended. You may experience incompatibility problems or a conflict between different manufacturer network drivers.
\par 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf1\i IPX / SPX Protocol LAN Connection Problems
\par \plain\f2\fs20 It is important to check the properties of your network settings within your Windows\plain\f4\fs20 \'e2\plain\f2\fs20  control panel. You must ensure that this section has included within it an IPX / SPX compatible protocol. If this is not included you may alternatively require a Novell\plain\f4\fs20 \'e2\plain\f2\fs20  IntranetWare IPX 32bit protocol for your system. 
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs20\cf1 
\par \pard\ri-37\plain\f2\fs20 If you select IPX / SPX as the protocol, you must have SPX available as well as IPX. In some circumstances it may be possible that only IPX is available, in this case the IPX/SPX protocol button should be disabled automatically. This protocol has been tested with the IPX/SPX provided with Windows 95/98, it is unsure how any other IPX protocol provider may behave.
\par 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf1\b\i 8.3\tab TCP/IP Protocol
\par 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf1\i TCP/IP Protocol LAN Connection\plain\f2\fs20 
\par Connection under LAN is very simple as Worms Armageddon will automatically look for IP addresses running the game.
\par 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf1\i TCP/IP Protocol Internet Connection
\par \plain\f2\fs20 You need a TCP/IP connection (and a valid IP address, dynamic or fixed) in order to play via the Internet and connect to a Worms Armageddon game server or other user via direct connection.
\par 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf1\i TCP/IP Protocol Connection Problems
\par \plain\f2\fs20 If you are experiencing problems with connection please find a few possible solutions below to alleviate your problem. Please note that if you are connecting via the Internet, some online services such as AOL\plain\f4\fs20 \'e3\plain\f2\fs20  or Compuserve\plain\f4\fs20 \'e3\plain\f2\fs20  may automatically have become inactive if you have not accessed for a given period. Note that if you cannot obtain an Internet connection at all then you should really contact your network administrator or ISP for a viable solution.
\par 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf1\i Ping Command
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs20 Despite our best endeavours, we cannot control the speed of connections and data flow over the Internet. This option within the network menu allows you to establish if your IP address and other IP addresses are currently active and working. It also determines the general overall quality of your Internet connection to other players. This sends a small amount of data to another specified computer IP address and estimates the incurred time period for transfer to and from it.
\par 
\par \plain\f2\fs20\cf1\i Kick Player
\par \plain\f2\fs20 If you are hosting a game and feel that a poor Internet connection is likely to affect the general performance of the game, you may opt to exclude a given player.\plain\f2\fs20\b 
\par \plain\f2\fs20  
\par \pard\ri-37\plain\f2\fs20\cf1\i Winipcfg Command
\par \plain\f2\fs20 In Worms Armageddon your IP address can be obtained from within the network screen under your connected machine name. However on some systems, especially if you have two possible Internet connection methods such as a network card and a dial-up adapter you will have to use the winipcfg command within Windows to establish your active IP address.
\par 
\par From the Windows startbar select 'Run\'85' and in the text box now type 'winipcfg'. When selecting 'OK' a window should be displayed. This contains all the relevant information relating to your IP configuration including your currently active IP address.
\par \pard\plain\f2\fs20 
